The paper proposes a model for real-time background subtraction using AGMM, which is a common technique used in computer vision and image processing, indicating that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of adaptive techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the robustness of the proposed model, indicating that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the proposed model for surveillance, which suggests that it could also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
